  "explanation": "## NOT Gate (IPTG)\n**Pattern:** Logic Not\n**Organism:** Escherichia coli\n\n### Description\nInverter: output (GFP) is ON when IPTG is absent, OFF when present\n\n### Transcription Units\n- **output_promoter**: PLlacIq Promoter -> RBS B0034 -> GFP (Green Fluorescent Protein) -> Double Terminator B0015 (932 bp)\n- **input_promoter**: PLlac/ara Promoter -> RBS B0034 -> LacI Repressor -> Double Terminator B0015 (1405 bp)\n\n### Regulatory Connections\n- input_promoter --[activates]--> inverter_repressor\n- inverter_repressor --[represses]--> output_promoter\n- output_promoter --[activates]--> output_reporter\n\n### Component Details\n- **input_promoter** (promoter): PLlac/ara Promoter -- IPTG-inducible promoter from the lac operon. Repressed by LacI, induced by IPTG.\n- **inverter_repressor** (repressor): LacI Repressor -- Lac repressor protein. Binds lac operator and represses transcription. IPTG releases LacI.\n- **output_promoter** (promoter): PLlacIq Promoter -- Hybrid lac/tet promoter. Repressed by LacI, induced by IPTG.\n- **output_reporter** (reporter): GFP (Green Fluorescent Protein) -- Green fluorescent protein. Emits at 509 nm.\n\n**Total construct:** ~2337 bp across 2 transcription unit(s)",
